      "content": "I see. So, even though both committed the exact same non-violent offense, it sounds like the court uses their background to predict their future behavior. If we look at the actual goal of sentencing—which is often rehabilitation—wouldn't it actually make more sense to prioritize intensive community support and vocational training for Defendant B, since he lacks the stable foundation that Defendant A already has? Why wouldn't the law treat his lack of stability as a reason to provide *more* support rather than a reason to punish him more harshly?",
